<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="442" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,152,179]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[358,523,153,179]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[358,523,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are distributed along the coastline of the Iberian Peninsula from the southern Atlantic slope of 
<collectingCountry box="[391,455,189,215]" name="Spain" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Spain</collectingCountry>
(lower Guadalquivir region) to 
<collectingRegion box="[819,929,189,215]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
, plus the Oued Saoura basin in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,235,225,251]" name="Algeria" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blanco, J. L. &amp; Hrbek, T. &amp; Doadrio, I." box="[250,460,225,251]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="39 - 53" refId="ref17752" refString="Blanco, J. L., Hrbek, T. &amp; Doadrio, I. (2006) A new species of the genus Aphanius (Nardo, 1832) (Actinopterygii, Cyprinodontidae) from Algeria. Zootaxa, 1158 (1), 39 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1158.1.2" type="journal article" year="2006">
Blanco 
<emphasis box="[337,386,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Doadrio, I. &amp; Carmona, J. A. &amp; Fernandez-Delgado, C." box="[471,691,225,251]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="67 - 79" refId="ref18176" refString="Doadrio, I. Carmona, J. A. &amp; Fernandez-Delgado, C. (2002) Morphometric study of the Iberian Aphanius (Actinopterygii: Cyprinodontiformes), with description of a new species. Folia Zoologica, 51, 67 - 79." type="journal article" year="2002">
Doadrio 
<emphasis box="[569,625,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gonzales, E. G. &amp; Pedraza-Lara, C. &amp; Doadrio, I." box="[702,933,225,251]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="597 - 610" refId="ref19429" refString="Gonzales, E. G., Pedraza-Lara, C. &amp; Doadrio, I. (2014) Genetic diversity and population history of the endangered killifish Aphanius baeticus. Journal of Heredity, 105, 597 - 610. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jhered / esu 034" type="journal article" year="2014">
Gonzales 
<emphasis box="[813,862,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[956,1039,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1711,1736]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,781,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,777,1686]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 14. Records of Apricaphanius and Tellia species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3943909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3943909/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Other records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1363,225,251]" name="Algeria" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Algeria</collectingCountry>
represented in 
<figureCitation box="[258,367,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1711,1736]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,781,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,777,1686]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 14. Records of Apricaphanius and Tellia species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3943909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3943909/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Figure 14</figureCitation>
are based on historic records of fishes identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1049,261,287]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iberus">
<emphasis box="[948,1049,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">A. iberus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pellegrin, J." box="[1091,1273,261,287]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 216" refId="ref20513" refString="Pellegrin, J. (1921) Le poissons des eaux douces de l'Afrique du Nord Francaise, Maroc, Tunisie, Sahara. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences naturelles du Maroc, 1 (2), 1 - 216, 96 figs." type="book chapter" year="1921">Pellegrin (1921)</bibRefCitation>
and may have been populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[379,529,297,323]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saourensis">
<emphasis box="[379,529,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">A. saourensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but none have been confirmed since.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="442" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,333,359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Etymology.</emphasis>
Based on the Latin substantive 
<emphasis box="[685,772,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricus</emphasis>
, shining, for the many small white spots on the flanks of the male, which give them a shiny appearance. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="442" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,405,431]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Remarks.</emphasis>
The molecular phylogeny presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hrbek, T. &amp; Kucuk, F. &amp; Frickey, T. &amp; Stolting, K. N. &amp; Wildekamp, R. H. &amp; Meyer, A." box="[768,984,405,431]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref19662" refString="Hrbek, T., Kucuk, F., Frickey, T., Stolting, K. N., Wildekamp, R. H. &amp; Meyer, A. (2002) Molecular phylogeny and historical biogeography of the Aphanius (Pisces, Cyprinodontiformes) species complex of central Anatolia, Turkey. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 25, 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.18864 / iujfas. 3778" type="journal article" year="2002">
Hrbek 
<emphasis box="[846,902,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[1072,1237,405,431]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[1072,1237,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister genus to all Aphaniids, except 
<taxonomicName authority=", Paraphanius" authorityName="Paraphanius" box="[398,678,441,467]" genus="Aphaniops" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[398,518,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Aphaniops</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[533,678,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Paraphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1853" box="[735,798,441,467]" genus="Tellia" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,798,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Tellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The molecular tree published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Esmaeili, H. R. &amp; Teimori, A. &amp; Zarei, F. &amp; Gholami, S." box="[1189,1436,441,467]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="0231717" refId="ref18541" refString="Esmaeili, H. R., Teimori, A., Zarei, F. &amp; Gholami, S. (2020) DNA barcoding and species delimitation of the Old World toothcarps, family Aphaniidae Hoedeman, 1949 (Teleostei: Cyprinodontiformes). PLoS ONE, 15 (4), e 0231717. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0231717" type="journal article" year="2020">
Esmaeili 
<emphasis box="[1296,1353,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[232,397,477,503]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[232,397,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[501,624,477,503]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Esmaeilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[501,624,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Esmaeilius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Geiger, M. F. &amp; Herder, F. &amp; Monaghan, M. T. &amp; Almada, V. &amp; Barbieri, R. &amp; Bariche, M. &amp; Berrebi, P. &amp; Bohlen, J. &amp; Casal-Lopez, M. &amp; Delmastro, G. B. &amp; Denys, G. P. J. &amp; Dettai, A. &amp; Doadrio, I. &amp; Kalogianni, E. &amp; Karst, H. &amp; Kottelat, M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Laporte, M. &amp; Lorenzoni, M. &amp; Marcic, Z. &amp; Ozulug, M. &amp; Perdices, A. &amp; Perea, S. &amp; Persat, H. &amp; Porcelotti, S. &amp; Puzzi, C. &amp; Robalo, J. &amp; Sanda, R. &amp; Schneider, M. &amp; Slechtova, V. &amp; Stoumboudi, M. &amp; Walter, S. &amp; Freyhof, J." box="[709,935,477,503]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="1210 - 1221" refId="ref18998" refString="Geiger, M. F., Herder, F., Monaghan, M. T., Almada, V., Barbieri, R., Bariche, M., Berrebi, P., Bohlen, J., Casal-Lopez, M., Delmastro, G. B., Denys, G. P. J., Dettai, A., Doadrio, I., Kalogianni, E., Karst, H., Kottelat, M., Kovacic, M., Laporte, M., Lorenzoni, M., Marcic, Z., Ozulug, M., Perdices, A., Perea, S., Persat, H., Porcelotti, S., Puzzi, C., Robalo, J., Sanda, R., Schneider, M., Slechtova, V., Stoumboudi, M., Walter, S. &amp; Freyhof, J. (2014) Spatial heterogeneity in the Mediterranean Biodiversity Hotspot affects barcoding accuracy of its freshwater fishes. Molecular Ecology Resources, 14, 1210 - 1221. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / 1755 - 0998.12257" type="journal article" year="2014">
Geiger 
<emphasis box="[793,851,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
, placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[1029,1194,477,503]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1194,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nardo" authorityYear="1827" box="[1330,1436,477,503]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Aphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[200,354,513,539]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[200,354,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their analysis of Mediterranean species (
<figureCitation box="[854,921,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,964,989]" captionTargetBox="[187,1401,345,938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[187,1401,345,939]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Two-way demonstration of basic cladograms of Aphaniid genera against their character states. Cladograms were simplified and drawn by adapting phylogenetic trees provided by previous studies. Black bars represent presence and white bars represent absence of the corresponding character state. Small dots within the bars stand for the presence of exceptional species to the general state." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3943883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3943883/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The results of these studies clearly demon- strate that 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[274,439,549,575]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[274,439,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be placed in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[685,839,549,575]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[685,839,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that it represents a distinct, well-distinguished phylogenetic group. To avoid paraphyly, 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[620,785,585,611]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[620,785,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be treated as a distinct genus despite its superficial similarity to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[294,448,621,647]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,448,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[199,364,657,683]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[199,364,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[419,573,657,683]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[419,573,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species lack head canals and possess pelvic fins, a dermal sheath at the analfin base in the nuptial female, and a single row of tricuspid teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">
Male 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[265,430,729,755]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[265,430,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[488,642,729,755]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[488,642,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess a black dorsal-fin margin, which is narrow in 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[1271,1436,729,755]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1436,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vs. wide, often the entire dorsal fin is black in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[680,834,765,791]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,834,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Male 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[922,1087,765,791]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[922,1087,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are well distinguished from all 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[151,305,801,827]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,305,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by presence of a white or hyaline sub-marginal band in the dorsal fin often with some isolated brown spots or blotches (vs. absence in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[522,676,837,863]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[522,676,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Male 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[764,929,837,863]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[764,929,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
either lack flank bars (
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1341,837,863]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saourensis">
<emphasis box="[1190,1341,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">A. saourensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or possess 12–22 narrow, irregular set and shaped flank bars which are usually split vertically and overlaid with numerous minute whitish spots in adults (vs. 5–13 regularly set and shaped bars, not overlaid by spots in all but one 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wildekamp" baseAuthorityYear="1993" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species). Male 
<taxonomicName box="[400,662,945,971]" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="species" species="villwocki">
<emphasis box="[400,662,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys villwocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess 13–25 narrow brown flank bars, but also 4–14 vertical rows of small black or brown spots in the caudal fin (vs. 1–4 bold black bars in 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[982,1147,981,1007]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[982,1147,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">
The flank bars are not very easy to see in male 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[719,884,1017,1043]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[719,884,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since the flank bars and dorsal-fin colour pattern often dissociate in adult individuals larger than 
<quantity box="[679,757,1052,1079]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
SL. The flank pattern in the adult male 
<taxonomicName genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys irregularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also comprises numerous small white spots (
<bibRefCitation author="Yogurtcuoglu, B. &amp; Freyhof, J." box="[713,1059,1089,1115]" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" pagination="319 - 330" refId="ref21949" refString="Yogurtcuoglu, B. &amp; Freyhof, J. (2018) Aphanius irregularis, a new killifish from south western Anatolia (Cyprinodontiformes: Aphaniidae). Zootaxa, 4410 (2), 319 - 330. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4410.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">Yoğurtçuoğlu &amp; Freyhof 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and this is also the case in some species of 
<emphasis box="[270,415,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Paraphanius</emphasis>
such as 
<taxonomicName box="[510,645,1125,1151]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Paraphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[510,645,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">P. alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[700,842,1125,1151]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Paraphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mentoides">
<emphasis box="[700,842,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">P. mentoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We suspect the presence of small white spots on the flank has evolved at least four times in 
<taxonomicName box="[588,720,1161,1187]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Aphaniidae</taxonomicName>
, and its occurrence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu, 2020" authorityName="Freyhof &amp; Yoğurtçuoğlu" authorityYear="2020" box="[969,1134,1161,1187]" class="Actinopteri" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Apricaphanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[969,1134,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Apricaphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority=", Paraphanius" authorityName="Paraphanius" genus="Anatolichthys" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Anatolichthys irregularis, Paraphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1853" box="[350,413,1197,1223]" genus="Tellia" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="21" pageNumber="442" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[350,413,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="442">Tellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the result of convergent evolution.
</paragraph>
